title: Holding of 7th session of political consultations between Algeria, Argentina
text: As part of strengthening bilateral relations between Algeria and Argentina and in order to give a new dynamic cooperation between the two countries, the work of the 7th session of political consultations between the two countries took place at the headquarters of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the National Community abroad,on November 22, 2022.

The Algerian delegation was chaired by Ambassador Mohamed Berrah, Director General America, while the Argentine delegation was chaired by Claudio Javier Rozencwaig, Under secretary for Foreign Policy at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Worship.

The two sides took this opportunity to discuss ways to strengthen bilateral relations and their promotion to the highest levels, and this, given the common interests and significant potential of the two countries.
They also welcomed the holding of this session of political consultations which will give new impetus to bilateral cooperation at all levels.Â

The two officials have reiterated, moreover, the readiness of their countries to continue and strengthen the political dialogue, and agreed on the need to strengthen high-level visits between the two countries, in addition to holding new sessions of the Intergovernmental Committee and the bilateral scientific committee at the beginning of next year.
